title: Week 5: ALL-USA South Dakota top performers
text:
Week 5: ALL-USA South Dakota top performers David Nicholson , dnicholson@argusleader.com 11:34 p.m. CDT October 1, 2015 Dodi Makwinja runs against Brandon Valley in September. Makwinja rushed 15 times for 128 yards and two scores in the Knights’ 42-10 win over Watertown last Friday. (Photo: Emily Spartz Weerheim / Argus Leader) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
With just four weeks left in the season, teams are settling in for across-class skirmishes and divisional disputes. As the season enters the stretch run, here’s a look back at this week’s top performers with the American Family Insurance ALL-USA South Dakota Players of the Week: 
Platte-Geddes picked up its first win of the season Friday night with a 48-24 win over Sunshine Bible Academy. 
Parker Boyden led Platte-Geddes to its first win of the season with 11 carries for 168 yards and three touchdowns against Sunshine Bible Academy. Boyden also had a 62-yard touchdown pass. 
Langford Area’s Lincoln Gibbs rushed 24 times for 284 yards while Chance Olson added 13 carries for 151 yards in the Lions’ 45-23 defeat of Warner. 
Madison’s Brodie Frederiksen rushed for 167 yards and five touchdowns in the top-ranked Bulldogs’ 48-15 win over Vermillion. 
Keegan Van Egdom needed just 12 carries to amass 251 yards and three touchdowns as Sioux Falls Christian blanked Flandreau 43-0. Tyler Leisinger and co. tasked with cracking Trojans’ staunch defense 
Brookings’ Gerald Maxwell followed a 225-yard performance against Lincoln with a 162 yards in Brookings’ 54-12 win over Huron. 
O’Gorman’s Dodi Makwinja rushed 15 times for 128 yards and two scores in the Knights’ 42-10 win over Watertown. Luke Fritsch added 108 yards and two scores on 14 attempts. 
Brandon’s Chase Grode caught five passes for 86 yards and returned an interception 72 yards for a score as the Lynx topped Harrisburg 30-6. 
Lincoln’s Lee Ransom had five catches for 89 yards and a touchdown, and also scored on a 63-yard reverse as the Patriots defeated Aberdeen Central 28-0. 
Reed Harter finished with six touchdowns – four passing and two rushing – as Colome upended Avon 56-22. Harter rushed for 163 yards and threw for 125 more.
